    </div>
    <p>This test measures sight word vocabulary grade level. It measures ability to pronounce words at different levels of ability. A sight word reading level is attained.</p>
</div>

<div class="px-3 py-2 blue_box mt-4 border border-2 bg-opacity-10">
    <div>
        <div class="d-flex flex-row">
            <p class="fs-5 fw-bold form-label">Directions / Test Specific Observations</p>
            <div class="green_line"></div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div>
        <div>
            <div class="heading_size">A. DIRECTIONS</div>
            <div class="print-row list_size">
                <div class="px-4 col-6">
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            <ul class="ps-0" style="list-style-type:none;">
                                <li class="pb-2">Print the Huntington Sight Word Assessment Teacher Copy or have it open on the screen to mark correct answers.</li>
                                <li>Before administering the Huntington Sight Word Assessment, open the PDF document for he Word Lists and have it ready to share on Zoom.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Says,
                            <ul style="list-style-type:disc" class="italic_font">
                                <li>"I am going to show you a list of words on the computer screen."</li>
                                <li>"I want to see how many of these words you can read.</li>
                                <li>Please begin here and read each word aloud as carefully as you can.</li>
                                <li>When you come to a difficult word, do the best you can</li>
                                <li> If you can't read it, say `blank' and go to the next one."</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Start 2 grades below present grade. The student must attain 20 out of 20 correct on the starting list. If your first starting list is less than 20 correct, move down until the student meets this criterion. Tell the student to attempt as many lists as possible without becoming frustrated.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                <div class="px-4 col">
                    <ol start="4">
                        <li>
                            Once the student achieves 20 on any list, go forward until the student reaches a list wherethe student is only able to read 10 words or less correctly
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            When the student has difficulty and is hesitant, reluctant, or too embarrassed to continue, say, <span class="italic_font">"Look quickly down this list and read the words you think you know."</span>Do this until it becomes too difficult; then stop.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            If possible, write the word pronounced on your sheet.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            SCORE IMMEDIATELY TO DETERMINE ANY TESTINH EXCEPTIONS. See GENERAL LC TEST SCORINH.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Check C for correct words and I for incorrect words. Count number correct and indicate at bottom of each list
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="heading_size">B. TEST SPECIFIC OBSERVATIONS</div>
            <div class="print-row list_size">
